= Bind Materials By Collection Name =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Automatically binds materials to primitives by matching collection names to material names."""

== Overview ==

Bind Materials By Collection Name iterates over all collections under the specified __Collections__ path and looks for a material under __Materials__ with the same name. When a match is found, a material binding is applied to the target __Primitive__.

This is particularly useful for crowd workflows where collection names correspond directly to material names.

@parameters

Collections:
    #id: collections
    Root prim path containing the USD collections. Default: `/collections`.

Materials:
    #id: materials
    Root prim path containing the USD materials. Default: `/materials`.

Primitive:
    #id: prim
    Target primitive to receive the material bindings. Default: `/crowd`.
